heir future” grade has served as sysco’s senior vice president of finance and chief accounting officer since early  with responsibility for field finance commercial finance financial planning and analysis financial reporting and shared services accounting he began his career at sysco as a staff auditor in  and has since held a variety of senior finance and commercial roles including chief financial officer of sysco chicago in  followed by chief financial officer of sysco canada in  he was later promoted to president of sysco canada in  and then became senior vice president of foodservice operations north region and canada in  grade earned an undergraduate degree in accounting and finance with a specialization in international business from the university of wisconsinmadison in  and an mba in finance strategy and marketing from northwestern university’s kellogg school of management in  “as a veteran sysco leader with nearly  years of experience in key finance and commercial roles joel is uniquely suited to step into the cfo position” delaney said “his deep knowledge of our local operations and people combined with his more recent service at the corporate level give him a wellrounded view of how to better serve our customers we are fortunate to have a leader like joel ready to take on this key position and i look forward to working closely with him in his new role as we move forward” about sysco sysco is the global leader in selling marketing and distributing food products to restaurants healthcare and educational facilities lodging establishments and other customers who prepare meals away from home its family of products also includes equipment and supplies for the foodservice and hospitality industries the company operates  distribution facilities serving approximately  customers for fiscal year  that ended june   the company generated sales of more than  billion for more information visit wwwsyscocom or connect with sysco on facebook at wwwfacebookcomsyscocorporati